  "repo_truth": "Fresh read-only review of the exact complete HCM-2.2 twelve-times-remediated planning subject. It freezes future implementation contracts but contains no product implementation, grants no implementation authority before clean closeout, and carries no clean-review conclusion.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay the sorted complete manifest and aggregate fingerprint before review.",
    "Review every subject byte: 00, 04, 06, twelve immutable prior dispatches, SPEC, all exact contract/schema/vector/JCS/transcript/API/security/waiver fixtures, plan, unchecked todo, planning proof, and twelve remediation records.",
    "Read unchanged 01, 02, 03, 05, 07, 08, HCM-0.6 decision, selected HCM-2.1 record/packet/proof, exact live definition assets, and engine/compiler/flow/CLI/skill/template/test sources only as needed.",
    "Run bounded read-only exact schema/JCS/fingerprint/profile/intake, runtime cross-record, CTAP2/ES256, bootstrap ownership, security bound, waiver order, final-use lockout, cross-family recovery, admin DTO, transaction, Markdown/link, Git, handoff, bridge, and classification checks.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence through the built-in channel."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No edits, staging, commits, new dispatches, global handoffs, ledger writes, or user task hops.",
    "No Rust, Cargo, production definitions, runtime fixtures/tests/product/generated-skill/pipeline, HCM-2.3+, Phase-3, SDK, Tauri, Substrate, contract, dock, or publication implementation.",
    "Do not invent alternate schema/intake bytes, bootstrap mappings, record partition, fingerprint/ref behavior, approval/waiver/identity/registry/use-chain trust, transaction visibility, lifecycle, renderer, migration, compatibility, bridge, or sibling scope.",
    "Do not treat prior findings, passing reproduction, or contingent planning status as proof that the 52-entry subject is clean."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke required skills in order, remain read-only, replay the exact complete manifest/aggregate, and return BLOCKED if any byte differs.",
    "Review findings first in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order with exact file/line, violated authority, failure, smallest remediation, and missing or invalidated proof.",
    "Reproduce ten schema entries, eleven definition JCS vectors, thirteen runtime identities/six schema validations/real registry-resolved DER ES256, twelve positive and sixteen negative admin vectors, seven transcripts, strict CBOR/P-256, 16 profile schema sources, dependency graph, closure fingerprints, old-byte preservation, and independent encoders/decoders.",
    "Verify bootstrap accepts quorum without caller mappings, derives only sorted quorum plus fixed registry-admin mappings in-engine, and refuses arbitrary/fixed/extra supplied mappings before native I/O; verify all 30 collection/raw bounds and exact/changed/one-over algorithm cases.",
    "Verify unique waiver refs/fingerprints, approval tuple sort, challenge lowercase sort, two permutation normalizations, duplicate and unsorted refusals before hash/native I/O, schema uniqueItems, and exact approval-policy closure semantics.",
    "Verify sequence-4095 final-use-only behavior preserves a distinct usable covering credential, same-transaction replacement visibility, alternate-admin exhaustion recovery, sole-admin ordinary refusal, and crash/marker recovery with no lockout window.",
    "Verify opaque CTAP transport, corrected response-registration-state-transition identity, response-inclusive paths, exact admin results/refusals, complete journal record sets, shared cross-family use recovery, global lock order, retained observations, canonical/Markdown fixtures, C03/C04, product cutover, bridges, proof/deletion gates, planning-only status, primary commit, and separate parent closeout.",
    "Return CLEAN only if no valid Critical or Required finding remains; otherwise CHANGES_REQUIRED or BLOCKED. Make no edits."
  ],
